text: Proshermacha is a genus of mygalomorph spiders in the family Anamidae, first described by Eugène Simon in 1908. ==Species== it contains eight species: *Proshermacha auropilosa (Rainbow & Pulleine, 1918) — Australia *Proshermacha cuspidata (Main, 1954) — Australia (Western Australia) *Proshermacha intricata (Rainbow & Pulleine, 1918) — Australia *Proshermacha maculata (Rainbow & Pulleine, 1918) — Australia *Proshermacha subarmata Simon, 1908 — Australia *Proshermacha tepperi (Hogg, 1902) — Southern Australia *Proshermacha tigrina Simon, 1908 — Australia *Proshermacha villosa (Rainbow & Pulleine, 1918) — Australia ==References== ==External links== Category:Mygalomorphae genera Category:Anamidae
title: Proshermacha
